   APP-LAYER EXEMPTION:

   Content you create using this framework is YOUR intellectual property
   and is NOT subject to the AGPL copyleft requirements. This includes:

     - Agent definitions you write in .claude/agents/
     - Compliance floor rules (compliance-floor.md)
     - Fleet configuration (fleet-config.json)
     - Application-specific memories (memory/app/)
     - Deployment scripts you write (ops/deploy.sh replacements)
     - Specialist agent templates you create
     - Skills you define in .claude/skills/
     - Any other project-specific configuration or content

   These are considered separable works that merely USE the framework
   interfaces and are not derivative works of the framework itself.

   The AGPL copyleft applies to modifications of the FRAMEWORK, meaning:

     - Core agent definitions (.claude/agents/ as shipped)
     - The collaboration protocol (.claude/COLLABORATION.md)
     - Metrics pipeline scripts (ops/metrics-log.sh, ops/dora.sh,
       ops/pathways.sh)
     - Hook infrastructure (.claude/settings.json schema)
     - Agent inheritance mechanism
     - Documentation style guide
     - Templates as shipped (templates/)

   If you modify these framework components and distribute the modified
   version or offer it as a network service, the AGPL requires you to
   make your modifications available under the AGPL.

